label: A5B_hR12_167_ce_b-001
title: Rhombohedral Al$_{5}$Mo Structure
comments:
Al$_{5}$Mo is known to have three phases (Schuster, 1991): \begin{itemize} \item Below 650K it is in a \href{current_web_home_dir/A5B_hR12_167_ce_b-001}{rhombohedral structure, Al$_{5}$Mo(r)} (this structure). \item Between 650K and 750-800K it is in a \href{current_web_home_dir/A5B_hP60_143_7a7b6c10d_3a3b4c-001}{trigonal structure, Al$_{5}$Mo(h')}. \item Above 750-800K up to 846K it is in the \href{current_web_home_dir/A5B_hP12_182_bcg_d-001}{Al$_{5}$W structure}. \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
 Hexagonal settings of this structure can be obtained with the option {\tt --hex}.
